('business:6-1-ethical-environmental:match:7ec0769f', 'business', 'business:6-1-ethical-environmental', '6.1 Ethical & Environmental', 'match', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which definition matches the key term “Fairtrade”?", "options": ["Resources that can only be used once and will run out, like oil and coal.", "Focusing on what is the ''right'' or ''wrong'' thing to do in business.", "The environmental consideration of how a business recycles or safely discards its rubbish.", "A movement encouraging a fair price to be paid to suppliers in developing countries."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "“Fairtrade” means: A movement encouraging a fair price to be paid to suppliers in developing countries."}'::jsonb),
